<div id="review_18649784" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/18649784" />
    <a title="Brad" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1022982-brad"><img alt="Brad" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442484575p2/1022982.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/18649784?book_show_action=true">Mar 25, 2008</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Brad" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Brad" href="/user/show/1022982-brad">Brad</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1022982-brad?shelf=about-life">about-life</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/1022982-brad?shelf=short-story">short-story</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer18649784" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16906237503581939111">I headed home dulled by work, dulled by the world around me, dulled by meaningless discourse, dulled by the apathy of others, dulled by the drift that&apos;s been pulling my mind away from the bones that hold it in, and as I approached the turn off to the beach I felt a pull I couldn&apos;t avoid, so I turned off. <br/><br/>Piano lessons were waiting. My kids were waiting. I needed to buy groceries. There was time, if I hurried, to spend with my love. But I found myself in the sand, shoes off, striding to the north</span>
  <span id="freeText16906237503581939111" style="display:none">I headed home dulled by work, dulled by the world around me, dulled by meaningless discourse, dulled by the apathy of others, dulled by the drift that's been pulling my mind away from the bones that hold it in, and as I approached the turn off to the beach I felt a pull I couldn't avoid, so I turned off. <br /><br />Piano lessons were waiting. My kids were waiting. I needed to buy groceries. There was time, if I hurried, to spend with my love. But I found myself in the sand, shoes off, striding to the north of the breakwater. Thinking. <br /><br />There was a piece of driftwood propped up against a piece of wave smoothed sandstone, and I was suddenly in the dark standing on the beach burning driftwood after an earthquake, watching the mutli-colours dance their midnight dance. <br /><br />I've not read this book in ages, but a piece of driftwood, of sunbleached, salt-soaked wood brought me back to the pages with ink on them that captured me a decade ago.<br /><br />I made it back in time for my lesson, but I missed spending time with my love. I am sad about that, but the driftwood was needed, so it's okay because next time we're together it will be richer for my detour.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16906237503581939111" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


